name: Venusaur-EX
Attack1Text: Your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Poisoned.
Attack2Text: Heal 30 damage from this Pokemon.

name: M Venusaur-EX
Attack1Text: Your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Paralyzed and Poisoned.

name: Caterpie
flavorText: It is covered with a green skin. When it grows, it sheds the skin, covers itself with silk, and becomes a cocoon.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Paralyzed.

name: Metapod
flavorText: Even though it is encased in a sturdy shell, the body inside is tender. It can't withstand a harsh attack.
Attack1Text: During your opponent's next turn, any damage done to this Pokemon by attacks is reduced by 40 (after applying Weakness and Resistance).
Attack2Text: Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Paralyzed.

name: Weedle
flavorText: Often found in forests and grasslands. It has a sharp, toxic barb of around two inches on top of its head.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Poisoned.

name: Kakuna
flavorText: This Pokemon is in a temporary stage while making its body. It is almost completely unable to move on its own.
Attack1Text: During your opponent's next turn, any damage done to this Pokemon by attacks is reduced by 40 (after applying Weakness and Resistance).
Attack2Text: Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Poisoned.

name: Beedrill
flavorText: May appear in a swarm. Flies at violent speeds, all the while stabbing with the toxic stinger on its rear.
Attack1Text: Your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Poisoned.
Attack2Text: This attack does 40 damage times the number of Beedrill you have in play to 1 of your opponent's Pokemon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokemon.)

name: Tangela
flavorText: Blue plant vines cloak the Pokemon's identity in a tangled mass. It entangles anything that gets close.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Paralyzed.
Attack2Text: Your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Poisoned.

name: Charmander
flavorText: From the time it is born, a flame burns at the tip of its tail. Its life would end if the flame were to go out.
Attack2Text: Discard a Fire Energy attached to this Pokemon.

name: Charmeleon
flavorText: It lashes about with its tail to knock down its foe. It then tears up the fallen opponent with sharp claws.
Attack2Text: Discard a Fire Energy attached to this Pokemon.

name: Charizard
flavorText: Its wings can carry this Pokemon close to an altitude of 4,600 feet. It blows out fire at very high temperatures.
Ability1Text: All Energy attached to this Pokemon are Fire Energy instead of their usual type.
Attack1Text: Discard 3 Energy attached to this Pokemon.

name: Charizard-EX
Attack2Text: This Pokemon can't use Combustion Blast during your next turn.

name: M Charizard-EX
Attack1Text: This Pokemon does 50 damage to itself.

name: Vulpix
flavorText: While young, it has six gorgeous tails. When it grows, several new tails are sprouted.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Confused.

name: Ninetales
flavorText: It has nine long tails and fur that gleams gold. It is said to live for 1,000 years.
Attack1Text: Switch 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokemon with his or her Active Pokemon. The new Active Pokemon can't retreat during your opponent's next turn.
Attack2Text: Discard a Fire Energy attached to this Pokemon.

name: Ninetales BREAK
Attack1Text: Discard all Fire Energy attached to this Pokemon. This attack does 60 more damage for each Energy card discarded in this way.

name: Growlithe
flavorText: Very friendly and faithful to people. It will try to repel enemies by barking and biting.
Attack1Text: Switch this Pokemon with 1 of your Benched Pokemon.

name: Arcanine
flavorText: A Pokemon that is described in Chinese legends. It is said to race at an unbelievable speed.
Ability1Text: Once during your turn (before your attack), if this Pokemon was on the Bench and became your Active Pokemon this turn, you may move any number of Fire Energy attached to your Pokemon to this Pokemon.
Attack1Text: This Pokemon can't attack during your next turn.

name: Ponyta
flavorText: Its body is light, and its legs are incredibly powerful. It can clear Ayers Rock in one leap.

name: Magmar
flavorText: Found near the mouth of a volcano. This fire-breather's body temperature is nearly 2,200 degrees Fahrenheit.
Attack2Text: Discard a Fire Energy attached to this Pokemon.

name: Blastoise-EX
Attack1Text: Switch this Pokemon with 1 of your Benched Pokemon. Then, your opponent switches his or her Active Pokemon with 1 of his or her Benched Pokemon.
Attack2Text: Flip a coin. If tails, this Pokemon does 30 damage to itself.

name: M Blastoise-EX
Attack1Text: This attack does 30 damage to 2 of your opponent's Benched Pokemon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokemon.)

name: Poliwag
flavorText: Its slick black skin is thin and damp. A part of its internal organs can be seen through the skin as a spiral pattern.

name: Poliwhirl
flavorText: Its two legs are well developed. Even though it can live on the ground, it prefers living in water.
Attack1Text: Choose 1 of your opponent's Active Pokemon's attacks. That Pokemon can't use that attack during your opponent's next turn.
Attack2Text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 50 damage times the number of heads.

name: Poliwrath
flavorText: An adept swimmer, it knows the front crawl, butterfly, and more. It is faster than the best human swimmers.
Attack1Text: If this Pokemon was on the Bench and became your Active Pokemon this turn, this attack does 50 more damage.
Attack2Text: Discard an Energy attached to your opponent's Active Pokemon.

name: Slowbro-EX
Attack1Text: Heal 60 damage from this Pokemon. This Pokemon can't attack during your next turn.

name: M Slowbro-EX
Attack1Text: This Pokemon is now Confused. During your next turn, this Pokemon's Loll Roll Spin attack does 100 more damage (before applying Weakness and Resistance).

name: Seel
flavorText: Covered with light blue fur, its hide is thick and tough. It is active in bitter cold of -40 degrees Fahrenheit.
Attack1Text: During your opponent's next turn, any damage done by attacks from the Defending Pokemon is reduced by 20 (before applying Weakness and Resistance).

name: Dewgong
flavorText: Its body is covered with a pure white fur. The colder the weather, the more active it becomes.
Attack1Text: Heal 40 damage from this Pokemon. Switch this Pokemon with 1 of your Benched Pokemon.
Attack2Text: This Pokemon does 20 damage to itself.

name: Staryu
flavorText: It appears in large numbers by seashores. At night, its central core flashes with a red light.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 10 more damage.

name: Starmie
flavorText: This Pokemon has a geometric body. Because of its body, the locals suspect that it is an alien creature.
Ability1Text: Once during your turn (before your attack), you may discard a card from your hand. If you do, put 2 basic Energy cards from your discard pile into your hand. (You can't choose a card you discarded with the effect of this Ability.)
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Paralyzed.

name: Starmie BREAK
Attack1Text: This attack does 100 damage to each of your opponent's Pokemon BREAK. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokemon.)

name: Magikarp
flavorText: It is virtually worthless in terms of both power and speed. It is the most weak and pathetic Pokemon in the world.
Attack1Text: This attack does 10 damage times the number of damage counters on this Pokemon.

name: Gyarados
flavorText: It has an extremely aggressive nature. The Hyper Beam it shoots from its mouth totally incinerates all targets.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Paralyzed.
Attack2Text: Flip 2 coins. If either of them is tails, this attack does nothing.

name: Pikachu
flavorText: It has small electric sacs on both its cheeks. If threatened, it looses electric charges from the sacs.
Attack2Text: Flip a coin. If tails, this Pokemon does 10 damage to itself.

name: Raichu
flavorText: Its electric charges can reach even 100,000 volts. Careless contact can cause even an Indian elephant to faint.
Attack1Text: Attach a Lightning Energy card from your discard pile to this Pokemon.
Attack2Text: You may discard all Energy attached to this Pokemon. If you do, this attack does 70 more damage.

name: Magnemite
flavorText: It moves while constantly hovering. It discharges Thunder Wave and so on from the units at its sides.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Paralyzed.
Attack2Text: This Pokemon does 50 damage to itself.

name: Magneton
flavorText: A linked cluster formed of several Magnemite. It discharges powerful magnetic waves at high voltage.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Paralyzed.
Attack2Text: This Pokemon does 80 damage to itself.

name: Voltorb
flavorText: A life-form whose identity is unknown. It is said to Screech or suddenly Self-Destruct.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin until you get tails. This attack does 10 damage times the number of heads.

name: Electrode
flavorText: It explodes in response to even minor stimuli. It is feared, with the nickname of "The Bomb Ball."
Ability1Text: Once during your turn (before your attack), you may Knock Out this Pokemon and attach it to one of your Lightning Pokemon as a Special Energy card. This card provides 2 Lightning Energy only while this card is attached to a Pokemon.

name: Electabuzz
flavorText: It loves to feed on strong electricity. It occasionally appears around large power plants and so on.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Paralyzed.
Attack2Text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 10 more damage. If tails, this Pokemon does 10 damage to itself.

name: Zapdos
flavorText: One of the legendary bird Pokemon. While it is flying, it makes crackling and snapping sounds.
Attack1Text: This Pokemon does 30 damage to itself.
Attack2Text: Discard all Energy attached to this Pokemon.

name: Nidoran ♂
flavorText: Its large ears are flapped like wings when it is listening to distant sounds. It extends toxic barbs when angered.
Attack1Text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 10 damage times the number of heads.

name: Nidorino
flavorText: It is easily angered. By swinging its well-developed horn wildly, it can even punch through diamond.
Attack2Text: Flip 3 coins. This attack does 30 damage times the number of heads.

name: Nidoking
flavorText: It is recognized by its rock-hard hide and its extended horn. Be careful with the horn as it contains venom.
Attack1Text: The Defending Pokemon can't retreat during your opponent's next turn.
Attack2Text: This attack does 20 damage to each of your opponent's Benched Basic Pokemon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokemon.)

name: Nidoking BREAK
Attack1Text: Your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Poisoned. Put 2 damage counters instead of 1 on that Pokemon between turns.

name: Gastly
flavorText: A being that exists as a thin gas. It can topple an Indian elephant by enveloping the prey in two seconds.
Attack1Text: During your opponent's next turn, if this Pokemon is Knocked Out by damage from an attack, discard an Energy attached to the Attacking Pokemon.
Attack2Text: Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Asleep.

name: Haunter
flavorText: If you get the feeling of being watched in darkness when nobody is around, Haunter is there.
Attack1Text: Your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Asleep.
Attack2Text: If your opponent's Active Pokemon is not Asleep, this attack does nothing.

name: Drowzee
flavorText: A descendant of the legendary animal baku, which is said to eat dreams. It is skilled at hypnotism.
Attack2Text: Your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Confused.

name: Koffing
flavorText: Its thin, balloon-like body is inflated by horribly toxic gases. It reeks when it is nearby.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Poisoned. If tails, your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Confused.

name: Mewtwo
flavorText: A Pokemon whose genetic code was repeatedly recombined for research. It turned vicious as a result.
Attack1Text: This attack does 20 more damage for each Energy attached to your opponent's Active Pokemon.
Attack2Text: During your opponent's next turn, prevent all effects of attacks, including damage, done to this Pokemon. If 1 of your Pokemon used Barrier during your last turn, this attack can't be used.

name: Mewtwo-EX
Attack1Text: Attach an Energy card from your discard pile to this Pokemon.
Attack2Text: Heal 60 damage from this Pokemon.

name: Mew
flavorText: So rare that it is still said to be a mirage by many experts. Only a few people have seen it worldwide.
Ability1Text: Prevent all effects of attacks, including damage, done to this Pokemon by your opponent's Evolution Pokemon.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Paralyzed.

name: Sandshrew
flavorText: It burrows and lives underground. If threatened, it curls itself up into a ball for protection.
Attack1Text: If the Defending Pokemon tries to attack during your opponent's next turn, your opponent flips a coin. If tails, that attack does nothing.

name: Diglett
flavorText: It burrows through the ground at a shallow depth. It leaves raised earth in its wake, making it easy to spot.
Ability1Text: As long as this Pokemon is on your Bench, prevent all damage done to this Pokemon by attacks (both yours and your opponent's).
Attack1Text: This attack does 30 damage to 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokemon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokemon.)

name: Dugtrio
flavorText: In battle, it digs through the ground and strikes the unsuspecting foe from an unexpected direction.
Attack2Text: This attack does 20 damage to each of your Benched Pokemon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokemon.)

name: Machop
flavorText: Its whole body is composed of muscles. Even though it's the size of a human child, it can hurl 100 grown-ups.
Attack1Text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 20 damage times the number of heads.

name: Machoke
flavorText: Its formidable body never gets tired. It helps people by doing work such as the moving of heavy goods.
Attack1Text: This attack does 60 damage minus 10 damage for each damage counter on this Pokemon.
Attack2Text: This Pokemon does 20 damage to itself.

name: Machamp
flavorText: Its four ruggedly developed arms can launch a flurry of 1,000 punches in just two seconds.
Ability1Text: If this Pokemon is your Active Pokemon and is damaged by an opponent's attack (even if this Pokemon is Knocked Out), put 3 damage counters on the Attacking Pokemon.

name: Machamp BREAK
Attack1Text: During your next turn, this Pokemon's attacks do 100 more damage to your opponent's Active Pokemon (before applying Weakness and Resistance).

name: Onix
flavorText: It usually lives underground. It searches for food while boring its way through the ground at 50 miles per hour.
Attack1Text: During your opponent's next turn, if this Pokemon would be damaged by an attack, prevent that attack's damage done to this Pokemon if that damage is 60 or less.

name: Hitmonchan
flavorText: The spirit of a pro boxer has infused this Pokemon. It throws punches that are faster than a bullet train.

name: Clefairy
flavorText: Its adorable appearance makes it popular as a pet. However, it is rare and difficult to find.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Asleep.
Attack2Text: Choose 1 of your opponent's Active Pokemon's attacks and use it as this attack.

name: Pidgeot-EX
Attack1Text: If this Pokemon was damaged by an attack during your opponent's last turn, this attack does the same amount of damage to your opponent's Active Pokemon.
Attack2Text: This attack does 20 damage to 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokemon. (Don't apply Weakness and resistance for Benched Pokemon.)

name: M Pidgeot-EX
Attack1Text: You may have your opponent switch his or her Active Pokemon with 1 of his or her Benched Pokemon.

name: Rattata
flavorText: Its fangs are long and very sharp. They grow continuously, so it gnaws on hard things to whittle them down.
Ability1Text: When you play this Pokemon from your hand onto your Bench, you may discard all Pokemon Tool cards attached to your opponent's Active Pokemon.

name: Raticate
flavorText: Its rear feet have three toes each. They are webbed, enabling it to swim across rivers.
Attack1Text: Discard an Energy attached to your opponent's Active Pokemon.
Attack2Text: This attack does 60 damage times the number of Special Energy cards in your opponent's discard pile.

name: Farfetch'd
flavorText: It always walks about with a plant stalk clamped in its beak. The stalk is used for building its nest.
Attack1Text: This Pokemon can't use Leek Slap during your next turn.

name: Doduo
flavorText: A two-headed Pokemon that was discovered as a sudden mutation. It runs at a pace of over 60 miles per hour.
Attack1Text: Flip 3 coins. This attack does 10 damage times the number of heads.

name: Chansey
flavorText: It lays several eggs a day. The eggs are apparently rich in nutrients and extremely delicious.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, prevent all damage done to this Pokemon by attacks during your opponent's next turn.
Attack2Text: This Pokemon does 80 damage to itself.

name: Porygon
flavorText: Using the most advanced technologies, scientists finally succeeded in making the first artificial Pokemon.
Attack1Text: Choose Grass, Fire, Water, Lightning, Psychic, Fighting, Darkness, Metal, Fairy, or Dragon type. The Defending Pokemon's Weakness is now that type until the end of your next turn. (The amount of Weakness doesn't change.)

name: Dragonite-EX
Ability1Text: When you play this Pokemon from your hand onto your Bench, you may put 2 Basic Pokemon (except for Dragonite-EX) from your discard pile into your hand.
Attack1Text: Discard an Energy attached to your opponent's Active Pokemon.

name: M Venusaur-EX
Attack1Text: Your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Paralyzed and Poisoned.

name: M Charizard-EX
Attack1Text: This Pokemon does 50 damage to itself.

name: M Blastoise-EX
Attack1Text: This attack does 30 damage to 2 of your opponent's Benched Pokemon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokemon.)

name: Mewtwo-EX
Attack1Text: Attach an Energy card from your discard pile to this Pokemon.
Attack2Text: Heal 60 damage from this Pokemon.

name: Pidgeot-EX
Attack1Text: If this Pokemon was damaged by an attack during your opponent's last turn, this attack does the same amount of damage to your opponent's Active Pokemon.
Attack2Text: This attack does 20 damage to 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokemon. (Don't apply Weakness and resistance for Benched Pokemon.)

name: M Pidgeot-EX
Attack1Text: You may have your opponent switch his or her Active Pokemon with 1 of his or her Benched Pokemon.

name: Dragonite-EX
Ability1Text: When you play this Pokemon from your hand onto your Bench, you may put 2 Basic Pokemon (except for Dragonite-EX) from your discard pile into your hand.
Attack1Text: Discard an Energy attached to your opponent's Active Pokemon.

name: ナッシー[Exeggutor]
flavorText: Dr.オーヤマ考案「日米交流カード」パーティ気分で和洋せっちゅう。
Attack1Text: コインを1回投げオモテなら、10ダメージを追加。 Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 10 more damage.

name: Flying Pikachu
flavorText: By learning how to fly, Pikachu overcame its weakness to Fighting Pokemon.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Paralyzed.
Attack2Text: Flip a coin. If tails, this attack does nothing. If heads, prevent all effects of attacks, including damage, done to this Pokemon during your opponent's next turn.

name: Surfing Pikachu
flavorText: One summer, a group of Pikachu was found riding the waves at the local beach.

name: Imakuni?'s Doduo
Ability1Text: When this Doduo retreats, hold this card and throw it as hard as you can because Doduo is running away. Throw the card horizontally with a snap to get the farthest distance!
Attack1Text: From the moment you use this attack, you must begin to sing a song. (While the song is being sung, the game continues.) When the song is finished, this attack does 30 damage.
